parameters: \pop[3]Hey, Dante. I have a question for you.
\pop[3]Well, it's just, you're such a funny guy...
\pop[3]I mean, I've read all of your books.
Your sense of humor doesn't slip in there at all.
You're \c[14]known\c[0] for all the drama and tragedy.
I kinda thought you'd be a different person.
\pop[4]I could say the same for you.
\pop[4]You're a completely different person when you're performing.
Those dance moves, that personality, it's just so... extravagant.
\pop[4]Then I guess my answer might be the same.
It's just what sells, and what I'm good at.
But now I have another question.
Like, if you had to describe it.
I don't feel like you're moments away from belting out a solo.
But actually, I think that's good. It's more like, the "real you".
\pop[4]Yeah. I think we all have our work personalities.
Even Isaac is a different guy on the clock.
\pop[4]Well I mastered my retail voice, for one.
It's super important when you work in sales.
\pop[4]Yeah. Just speak a higher pitch, with exaggerated enthusiasm.
\pop[4]I have some of the highest numbers in the district, so you tell me.
\pop[4]There you have it. We all act different when we're working.
But to answer "why"? I guess I use my writing as an outlet.
With all that dark stuff out of the way, I'm just left with what you get.
\pop[3]I bet you could write a good comedy, though.
\pop[4]Yeah, but then things would switch around.
A funny book would mean a dull Dante.
\pop[3]As if you're not dull enough already.
\pop[3]I can never pass when there's such a clear shot.
\pop[3]Wait. How is \c[14]Taylor\c[0] different when he works?
And here I thought it was a universal rule.
Your personality is the thing that sells you.
Can't afford to cover that up \c[14]or\c[0] make a fake one.
\pop[3]I'd take offense to that, but it's true.
I have to tell them that I'm the same in real life.
\pop[4]If I didn't know you, I'd find that one hard to believe.
I hope I don't kill the energy when I'm guesting.
Knowing how wild you can get, I'm kind of intimidated.
\pop[4]It might be a good time to tap your stage personality, then.
Your fans will all be watching, remember? They expect to see \c[14]you\c[0].
Or at the very least, the "you" they perceive you to be.
But I kind of like being the "real" me.
Haven't had much practice, but I'm enjoying this vacation.
\pop[3]Well it's just for one night, Klace.
As soon as it's over, you can go back to normal.
You don't have to act around us. We like you for who you are.
\pop[3]Thanks. I'm glad I got to meet Isaac, and everyone else, too.
Definitely made this hiatus worth fighting for.
Dante and Isaac have helped me out more times than I can count.
And when you need it, we'll be there to help you, too.
